						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the same temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājakēsarivarman i.e. Rājarāja I: Year lost.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription in three fragments is in Vaṭṭeḻuttu script. The first piece seems to record a sale executed in the village Kūttaṉkuḍi in Veṇbaikkuḍi-nāḍu the income of which was endowed for the drummers <hi rend="italic">(uvaichchar)</hi> who beat the drum by the merchant guild <hi rend="italic">Tisaiyāyira[ittaiññūṟṟuvar*].</hi> The other two fragments record a deed of sale for a value by the <hi rend="italic">nagarattār</hi> of Kūttaṉkuḍi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Udaiya [māttāṇḍapuram*] in Veṇbaikkuḍ-nāḍu and a gift to god Nārāyaṇa Viṇṇagaradēvar to provide for <hi rend="italic">tiruchcheṉṉaḍai</hi> by Araiyaṇ Vēḷaṉ Karuṅākaratādaṉ.</p>						

						</summary>
